<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--EscapeeArrested     11-05 0184</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Escapee Arrested,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Massachusetts Sex Offender Arrested in Los Angeles</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST COVINA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An armed escapee from a Massachusetts
treatment center for violent sexual criminals was arrested Saturday
after police got a tip inspired by a TV crime show.
   Christopher Rambert, 23, was arrested by police and FBI agents
at a motel in West Covina, about 20 miles east of downtown Los
Angeles, police said. A woman who was with him voluntarily was
released later.
   Police also recovered a semiautomatic pistol and a car reported
stolen in Georgia.
   A recent feature about Rambert on the Fox television show
``America's Most Wanted'' led to a tip that he was at the motel,
police said.
   Rambert was taken to a police station, where he agreed to put on
a T-shirt with the ``America's Most Wanted'' logo for his booking
photograph, police said. He was to be transferred to Los Angeles
County Jail to await extradition.
   Rambert escaped Oct. 1 from the center at a Bridgewater, Mass.,
prison, where he was serving a life sentence for multiple rapes and
other violent crimes, officers said.
