<FILEID>AP-NR-11-05-89 0941EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a BC-SFQuake-Aftershock     11-05 0154</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-SF Quake-Aftershock,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mild Aftershock Hits Quake-Rattled San Francisco Area</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MENLO PARK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mild aftershock to the destructive
Oct. 17 earthquake struck the San Francisco Bay area Sunday morning.
   Pat Jorgenson, a spokeswoman with the U.S. Geological Survey,
said the aftershock hit at 5:37 a.m. and measured 4.0 on the
Richter scale, according to a preliminary calculation. The
seismographic station at the University of California at Berkeley
estimated the strength at 4.2 on the scale.
   The quake occurred on the San Andreas fault and the epicenter
was in Loma Prieta, located about 8 miles northeast of Santa Cruz,
Ms. Jorgenson said.
   That is the same fault and epicenter of the Oct. 17 earthquake,
which measured 7.1 on the Richer scale, and claimed 66 lives and
billions of dollars in damage.
   There were no reports of damage or injuries. A 4.0 Richter quake
is capable of moderate damage near the center.
</TEXT>
