<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--PrawnSpawn     11-05 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Prawn Spawn,0119</SECOND>
<HEAD>Malaysia Shares Shrimp Tips</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Malaysia is sharing its
prawn-spawning prowess so other nations can learn how to breed the
big shrimp.
   Ong Kah Sin, the chief researcher at the Malaysian Fisheries
Department, said scores of countries are unable to domestically
breed prawns.
   Malaysia was able to produce about 150 million prawn spawns this
year after it picked up cultivation techniques from Japan, Ong
said. Now, the government has decided to open its own prawn
management course.
   Thirty-five people from Bahrain, Brunei, Egypt, Fiji, Ghana,
Iraq, Mauritius, Burma, Nigeria, the Philippines, Qatar, Swaziland,
Thailand, United Arab Emirates and Zambia are taking part in the
monthlong course that begins next year.
</TEXT>
