<FIRST>r i AM-Algeria-Quakes     11-05 0146</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Algeria-Quakes,0150</SECOND>
<HEAD>Earthquake Aftershocks Reported in Algeria</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALGIERS, Algeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two moderate aftershocks on Sunday
rumbled through an area struck by a strong quake last week, but
authorities reported no injuries or damage.
   The first struck at 12:40 p.m. and registered 4 on the Richter
scale, and it was followed by a temblor measure 3.5 about two
minutes later, the Algerian Center of Astronomy, Astrophysics and
Geophysics reported.
   Four other aftershocks, ranging from 3.5 to 4.2 on the scale,
were recorded by seismologists Saturday night.
   A quake registering 6 on the scale stuck the North African
country on Oct. 29 and was followed 12 minutes later by one
measuring 4.8. The quakes killed 26 people, injured at least 450,
and caused heavy damage to towns and villages along the
Mediterranean coast east of Algiers.
   The Richter scale gauges the energy released by an earthquake.
</TEXT>
