<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--India-Accident     11-05 0102</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--India-Accident,0103</SECOND>
<HEAD>25 Killed in Bus Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus on a northern mountain road
skidded and fell 250 feet into a gorge on Sunday, killing 25
passengers, United News of India reported.
   The news agency said 16 people also were seriously injured in
the accident which occurred in the Kinnaur district of Himachal
Pradesh state, 230 miles north of New Delhi.
   UNI did not say how many people were traveling in the
government-owned bus. The cause of the accident was not known, it
said. District officials and a team of doctors rushed to the remote
site.
